    <description><![CDATA[<p>Which of the following calls to the <code>add()</code> function are correct?</p>
<div class="code-block code-line-numbers open" style="counter-reset: code-block 0">
    <div class="code-header language-go">
        <span class="code-title"><i class="arrow fas fa-angle-right fa-fw" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
        <span class="ellipses"><i class="fas fa-ellipsis-h fa-fw" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
        <span class="copy" title="Copy to clipboard"><i class="far fa-copy fa-fw" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
    </div><div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-go" data-lang="go"><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="kd">func</span> <span class="nf">add</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">args</span> <span class="o">...</span><span class="kt">int</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="kt">int</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">    <span class="nx">sum</span> <span class="o">:=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="nx">_</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nx">arg</span> <span class="o">:=</span> <span class="k">range</span> <span class="nx">args</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">        <span class="nx">sum</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="nx">arg</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">    <span class="p">}</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl">    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="nx">sum</span>
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="cl"><span class="p">}</span></span></span></code></pre></div></div>
<ul>
<li>A. add(1, 2)</li>
<li>B. add(1, 3, 7)</li>
<li>C. add([]int{1, 2})</li>
<li>D. add([]int{1, 3, 7}&hellip;)</li>
</ul>
<button class="toggle-button" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('show')">ðŸ”‘ Answer Analysis:</button>
<div class="toggle-content">
  <p>A, B, D
<a href="https://go.dev/play/p/869njWxkuwY" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer ">Run online</a></p>
<p><a href="https://golang.google.cn/ref/spec#Passing_arguments_to_..._parameters" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer ">Go Official Documentation - Passing arguments to &hellip; parameters</a></p>
<p><code>add</code> is a variadic function that accepts any number of <code>int</code> type arguments.
The type of the <code>args</code> parameter is <code>...int</code>, which behaves as <code>[]int</code> (an <code>int</code> type slice) inside the function.
Although <code>[]int</code> and <code>...int</code> are both slices at the underlying level, Go&rsquo;s type system requires explicitly unpacking a slice as variadic parameters.</p>]]></description>
